the data from that database. A distributed graphql solution essentially bundles the seeds together, and wraps the orange meat together, giving us a single means to access data from all the databases.\n<img src=\"/Digital-Garden/assets/images/2021-12-02-10-49-11.png\"></p>\n<p>Distributed graphql can be achieved through schema stitching, Apollo Federation</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://netflixtechblog.com/how-netflix-scales-its-api-with-graphql-federation-part-1-ae3557c187e2\">more info</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"ue-resources\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#ue-resources\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>UE Resources</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.apollographql.com/blog/the-concepts-of-graphql-bc68bd819be3/#.hfczgtdsj\">Graphql concepts visualized</a>\n<a href=\"https://www.apollographql.com/blog/securing-your-graphql-api-from-malicious-queries-16130a324a6b/\">security (preventing DDOS)</a></p>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"backlinks\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#backlinks\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Backlinks</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/Digital-Garden/notes/MXSnfG3Cey0BozII19IQY\">GROQ</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"children\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#children\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Children</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/Digital-Garden/notes/yy5ylwnBHCQR8ef9dxldx\">AST</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/Digital-Garden/notes/pLjPOq1zALpEjYmeoRcI4\">Auth</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/Digital-Garden/notes/3HS5EsWWVemFJzEgHmi3j\">Client</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/Digital-Garden/notes/BbFQyn0yaYxYLIwA61LSm\">Fields</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/Digital-Garden/notes/uvNhRB7dp5lugyo3sUezc\">N1</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/Digital-Garden/notes/TX3jMpXN1gI4uQXGjbc0j\">Operations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/Digital-Garden/notes/hcBComYbCkiYKBV9G1o2L\